@name=John
@age=30
@base_url = https://postman-echo.com

### URL Encoded Form
POST {{base_url}}/post
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
Accept: application/json

name={{name}}&age={{age}}&city=NewYork

### Multipart Form with File Upload
POST {{base_url}}/post HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary_upload

------WebKitFormBoundary_upload
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="username"

admin
------WebKitFormBoundary_upload
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="email"

admin@example.com
------WebKitFormBoundary_upload
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="avatar"; filename="test.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

< ./upload_test.txt

------WebKitFormBoundary_upload

### Simple JSON POST
POST {{base_url}}/post
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "{{name}}",
  "age": {{age}}
}

### Multipart with Multiple Files
POST https://httpbin.org/post HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary_multipart

------Boundary_multipart
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="description"

This is a test upload with multiple files
------Boundary_multipart
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file1"; filename="variables.http"
Content-Type: text/plain

< ../variables.http
------Boundary_multipart
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file2"; filename="prompt.http"
Content-Type: text/plain

< ../prompt_variables.http
------Boundary_multipart


